    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-11T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="523"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.94/403</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-11T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1809. To <persName corresp="#p_BBM1">Baruch</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_SLL1">Summers</persName>:</p>
                <p>Maritime Transport Council has notified programme committees that recent changes
                    in tonnage situation necessitate general survey of shipping and requirements
                    position for cereal year ending August 31, 1919, and asks approximate
                    provisional estimate of requirements. We have not yet received replies to our
                    cables numbers 1450 and W133 seeking information for 1918 and 1919 programmes
                    for jute, flax, hemp, miscellaneous fibers.<note n="1" xml:id="d523fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> When may we expect such replies? Otherwise compelled to
                    proceed to best of our ability.</p>
                <p>Council further says, “the actual recorded consumption of civilian commodities
                    generally during past year shall be taken as setting the maximum limit for
                    programmes of importation during the ensuing year, this decision, however, not
                    preventing a different distribution as between the Allies or greater importation
                    of a particular commodity than last year where stocks have been used up and a
                    larger importation is required to avoid reduction of consumption. This principle
                    should be borne in mind in preparation of 1919 programme.”</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <persName>Patterson</persName>.</item>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
